703892f-b.title: Brooklyn: Cropsey Avenue - 14th Avenue
703892f-b.text:
Cropsey Ave., at its termination at Fourteenth Ave., in 1929,
showing Dyker Beach Park in an undeveloped state. The buildings of
the Polytechnic Preparatory Country Day School appear in the distance.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704052f-b.title: Brooklyn: Cropsey Avenue - 14th Avenue
704052f-b.text:
Dyker Beach Park: Viewed northwestward from Cropsey Ave., at Four-
teenth Ave., showing an artificial lake under construction. This is a
set of three views. In the background of views one and two is seen the
steeple of the Polytechnic Preparatory High School.
June 9, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.

704053f-a.title: Brooklyn: Cropsey Avenue - 14th Street
704053f-a.text:
Dyker Beach Park: From Cropsey Ave. at Fourteenth Ave., showing in
a set of three views looking northwest and southwest the made land in the
Park. In view No. 1 is seen the Polytechnic Preparatory School (towered,
building). In view No. 2 is seen a promontory, around which will be
extended 8hore Road.
June 9, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
